

\medskip
In the following problems, remember that by our conventions
$r \ge 0$.  Thus you should ignore any points where the equation would yield
$r < 0$.
\smallskip



\begin{enumerate}

\item  Sketch and identify the following graphs:

	(a) $r=2$.

	(b) $\theta =\frac{3\pi}{2}$.

	(c) $r=1-2\sin \theta$.

	(d) $r=3\cos 2\theta$.

	(e) $r^2=-2\cos2\theta$.

	(f) $r=\dfrac{3}{2+\sin\theta}$.\par

\answer{  In (c), $\pi/6 < \theta < 5\pi/6$ is excluded.
In (d), $\pi/4 < \theta < 3\pi/4$ and $5\pi/4 < \theta < 7\pi/4$
are excluded.  In (e), $0\le \theta < \pi/4$, $3\pi/4 < \theta
< 5\pi/4$, and $7\pi/4 < \theta \le 2\pi$ are excluded.
(e) looks approximately like (d) except it is rotated through
$\pi/2$.  (f) is an ellipse with center at $(0,-1)$.
